Amaduse OpenClaw Lab

This repository contains local integration code, documentation, tests, and
patch records for an unofficial OpenClaw-based Telegram imagebot.

OpenClaw compatibility patches target the OpenClaw npm package version recorded
in `patches/openclaw-2026.6.10-runtime/manifest.json` and
`policy/runtime_patch_contract.json`. The upstream OpenClaw package metadata for
version 2026.6.10 declares the MIT license and repository
`https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw.git`. Upstream OpenClaw copyrights and
license terms remain with the upstream project.

The mature projects and documentation referenced by this repository are design
references, not vendored source, unless a source file explicitly states
otherwise. See `docs/ATTRIBUTION_AND_REFERENCES.md` for the current reference
and attribution matrix.

This repository intentionally excludes bot tokens, provider secrets, browser
sessions, Telegram memories, generated media, raw logs, local OpenClaw runtime
state, and built binaries.
